The pizza here was legendary in the 90's. However,  this pizzeria is a shadow of its former glory. The pizza slices are still generous in size but the pizza itself has lowered in quality. The sauce is runny, the bread is undercooked and those things are over compensated with mounds of melted cheese. If you're a veggie lover like myself, do NOT add veggies to your pizza. It will only add insult to injury. I once bought a pie with green peppers and olives and the pizza was wet and flavorless. There are way too many pizzerias in the area to waste money here. My best bet would be Mama Tina's.
